bioghist.head: Historical/Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Honors Theses Collection includes original documents created by senior students in the Honors Program. Theses in Series I, II & III were given to the archives in 2005 by Professor Philip Elliot, Head of the Honors Program. This original group of theses is dated 1989-2002. The theses cover a broad range of subject areas and represent most academic departments. Most theses include a cover page with dates of review, the names of the reader/reviewer(s) and the name of the student advisor. This is an open collection. New theses are added at the end of the spring semester each year.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Series I - 1989-1994 - This series includes 23 theses representing a variety of topics including: biology, sociology, environmental earth science, history, communications, mathematics, economics and psychology.

Series II - 1995-1999 - This series includes 56 theses representing a variety of topics including: biology, history, mathematics & computer science, visual arts, English, communications, education, gender, business and political science.

Series III - 2000-2004 - This series includes 70 theses representing a variety of topics in the fields of education, biology, medicine, technology, health, psychology, communications, publishing, business, history, mathematics & computer science, philosophy, performing arts, gender, environmental studies, geography, literature and political science.

Series IV - 2005-2009 - This series currently includes [63] theses representing a variety of topics in the fields of communications, psychology, sociology, history, political science, athletics, visual art, literature, creative writing, medicine, biology, physical science, statistics, economics, mathematics and business.
